This paper deals with the performance analysis of IoT networks, specifically focusing on the uplink traffic scheduling and random access paradox. The paper utilizes stochastic geometry and queueing theory to develop a spatiotemporal mathematical framework to analyze and assess the performance of the two paradigms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and performance analysis (cs.PF).
